## Registry OBX Export/Import (Browse page)

### Context

Add a way to export one or several registry domains to a single `.obx`
(JSON) file from the Registry → Browse page and re-import the file later
with per-domain conflict resolution. The format carries an integer
`format_version` (1) plus `ontobricks_version` so future schema changes
stay backward-compatible via a small upgrader chain.

### Changes

1. `src/back/objects/registry/obx_format.py` *(new)*
   - `CURRENT_OBX_FORMAT_VERSION = 1`, upgrader registry, `build_envelope()`,
     and `load()` which validates the integer `format_version`, runs the
     upgrader chain when an older file is read, and enforces an optional
     `min_ontobricks_version` gate.

2. `src/back/objects/registry/__init__.py`
   - Re-export the new `obx_format` module and `CURRENT_OBX_FORMAT_VERSION`.

3. `src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py`
   - `export_registry_obx_result()` — builds the envelope from a spec
     `{domains: [{name, mode, versions?}]}` with mode in
     `{all, active, latest, selected}`.
   - `preview_obx_import_result()` — parses an uploaded `.obx`, returns
     per-domain conflict flags + a suggested rename.
   - `import_registry_obx_result()` — applies per-domain decisions
     (`skip` / `overwrite` / `rename`), defaulting to `skip` when missing.
   - 50 MB upload cap to protect the in-memory JSON parse.

4. `src/api/routers/internal/settings.py`
   - `POST /settings/registry/export` — streams the envelope as a JSON
     attachment (`ontobricks-YYYY-MM-DD.obx`); visibility-filtered via
     `filter_visible_domains`.
   - `POST /settings/registry/import/preview` — multipart preview.
   - `POST /settings/registry/import` — multipart import, gated by
     `require(ROLE_ADMIN)`.

5. `src/front/templates/partials/registry/_registry_domains.html`
   - Added Export / Import buttons; Import gated via
     `data-requires-app="admin"`.
   - Pulled in the two new modal partials.

6. `src/front/templates/partials/registry/_export_obx_modal.html` *(new)*
   - Per-domain checkbox + version mode selector (Latest / Active / All /
     Choose…) with per-version checkboxes when `Choose…` is picked.

7. `src/front/templates/partials/registry/_import_obx_modal.html` *(new)*
   - Two-step UX: file picker → preview (shows `format_version` and
     `ontobricks_version` of the file) → per-row Skip / Overwrite / Rename.

8. `src/front/static/registry/js/registry.js`
   - `openExportObxModal()`, blob download with `Content-Disposition`
     filename.
   - `openImportObxModal()`, preview rendering, decision collector with
     an overwrite-confirmation dialog before submission.

9. `tests/test_obx_format.py` *(new)*
   - 11 tests covering: missing/non-integer/future `format_version`,
     `min_ontobricks_version` gate, the upgrader chain pattern, malformed
     envelopes.

10. `tests/test_settings_obx.py` *(new)*
    - 13 tests covering export mode resolution, registry-not-configured
      guard, preview conflict flags, and the three import actions
      (skip/overwrite/rename), including the rename-conflict fallback.

### Modified files

- `src/back/objects/registry/obx_format.py` *(new)*
- `src/back/objects/registry/__init__.py`
- `src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py`
- `src/api/routers/internal/settings.py`
- `src/front/templates/partials/registry/_registry_domains.html`
- `src/front/templates/partials/registry/_export_obx_modal.html` *(new)*
- `src/front/templates/partials/registry/_import_obx_modal.html` *(new)*
