## Drop legacy LadybugDB field names from the runtime

### Context

LadybugDB is no longer a supported graph backend (Lakebase is the only
engine). The `dt_existence` payload still carried two legacy field names —
`local_lbug_exists` and `local_lbug_path` — that were reused but never
renamed when the backend changed. They surfaced into the consolidated
sync info endpoint and the front-end query-sync code, leading to confusing
field names. Plus a stale comment in `_export_obx_modal.html` still
mentioned `.lbug.tar.gz` (already fixed earlier today).

### Changes

1. `src/back/objects/digitaltwin/DigitalTwin.py`
   - Renamed `local_lbug_exists` → `graph_has_data` (Postgres table exists
     AND row count > 0; preserves the existing tri-state semantic).
   - Renamed `local_lbug_path` → `graph_display` (database·schema·table
     display string).

2. `src/back/objects/digitaltwin/_build_pipeline.py`
   - Same rename in the post-build session-cache writer. Dropped the
     now-empty `local_path` variable.

3. `src/back/objects/domain/HomeService.py`
   - Same rename in the consolidated `/dtwin/sync/info` payload.

4. `src/front/static/query/js/query-sync.js`
   - Reader rename, including the stale-cache override comment. Dropped
     the `eng === 'lakebase'` guard inside the override since there is no
     other engine to distinguish anymore.

5. `tests/test_home_service.py`
   - Updated fixture to use the new field names.

6. `src/front/templates/partials/registry/_export_obx_modal.html`
   *(already fixed earlier today)* — dropped the `.lbug.tar.gz` mention
   in the export-modal footer.

### Modified files

- `src/back/objects/digitaltwin/DigitalTwin.py`
- `src/back/objects/digitaltwin/_build_pipeline.py`
- `src/back/objects/domain/HomeService.py`
- `src/front/static/query/js/query-sync.js`
- `src/front/templates/partials/registry/_export_obx_modal.html`
- `tests/test_home_service.py`

### Test result

2003 passed — full suite green.
